Model Year Start: 2016 Model: Prius Prod Date Range: [11/2015 - 12/2018]
Title: EXTERIOR PANELS / TRIM: FRONT BUMPER: DISASSEMBLY; 2016 - 2018 MY Prius [11/2015 - 12/2018]

DISASSEMBLY

PROCEDURE

1. REMOVE FRONT SIDE ULTRASONIC SENSOR (w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System)

Click here

2. REMOVE ULTRASONIC SENSOR CLIP (w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System)

Click here

3. REMOVE FRONT CORNER ULTRASONIC SENSOR (w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System)

Click here

4. REMOVE FRONT CENTER ULTRASONIC SENSOR (w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System)

Click here

5. REMOVE FRONT SIDE ULTRASONIC SENSOR RETAINER (w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System)

Click here

6. REMOVE FRONT CORNER ULTRASONIC SENSOR RETAINER (w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System)

Click here

7. REMOVE NO. 3 ENGINE ROOM WIRE (w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System)

(a) w/o Fog Light:

(1) Disengage the 10 clamps and remove the No. 3 engine room wire.

(b) w/ Fog Light:

(1) Disengage the 10 clamps and remove the No. 3 engine room wire.

8. REMOVE MILLIMETER WAVE RADAR SENSOR ASSEMBLY (w/ Toyota Safety Sense P)

Click here

9. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER EXTENSION LH (w/o Fog Light)

(a) Remove the 2 screws.

(b) Disengage the claw to remove the front bumper extension LH.

10. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER EXTENSION RH (w/o Fog Light)

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the LH side.

11. REMOVE FOG LIGHT ASSEMBLY LH (w/ Fog Light)

Click here

12. REMOVE FOG LIGHT ASSEMBLY RH (w/ Fog Light)

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the LH side.

13. REMOVE FRONT FENDER LINER RETAINER

(a) Disengage the 2 claws to remove the 2 front fender liner retainers.

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

14. REMOVE HOOD TO FRONT END PANEL SEAL

(a) Separate the double-sided tape and disengage the 2 clips to remove the hood to front end panel seal.

Double-sided Tape

-

-

15. REMOVE RADIATOR GRILLE SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Remove the 2 screws and 4 clips.

(b) Disengage the 15 claws as shown in the illustration to remove the radiator grille sub-assembly.

Remove in this Direction

16. REMOVE NO. 3 AIR CLEANER INLET

(a) Remove the 2 screws.

(b) Disengage the 3 claws to remove the No. 3 air cleaner inlet.

17. REMOVE LOWER NO. 1 RADIATOR GRILLE

(a) Disengage the 18 claws as shown in the illustration to remove the lower No. 1 radiator grille.

Remove in this Direction

18. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER HOLE COVER LH

(a) Disengage the 2 claws as shown in the illustration.

*a

Hook

Remove in this Direction

(b) Disengage the hook to remove the front bumper hole cover LH.

19. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER HOLE COVER RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the LH side.

20. REMOVE RADIATOR GRILLE EMBLEM ASSEMBLY

(a) Check if there are slits at the positions shown in the illustration.

HINT:

The removal procedure for the radiator grille emblem assembly will differ depending on the existence of slits.

*a

Slit

-

-

(b) w/ Slit:

(1) Apply protective tape around the spring nut.

Protective Tape

(2) Using a plier nipper (side cutters), rotate the 2 spring nuts to align the cutouts of each spring nut as shown in the illustration.

*a

90

*b

Slit

*c

Cutout

-

-

(3) Using a plier nipper (side cutters), deform each spring nut as shown in the illustration and then remove the 2 spring nuts.

*a

Cutout

-

-

Pinch

-

-

(4) Disengage the 2 claws and 2 guides as shown in the illustration to remove the radiator grille emblem assembly.

Remove in this Direction

(c) w/o Slit (When Replacing the Radiator Grille Emblem Assembly):

(1) Apply protective tape around the spring nut.

Protective Tape

(2) Using a plier nipper (side cutters), cut the radiator grille emblem assembly at the positions shown in the illustration.

*a

Cut

(3) Push the radiator grille emblem assembly to remove the 2 spring nuts as shown in the illustration.

Push in this Direction

CAUTION:

Make sure to cover the spring nuts with a piece of cloth or equivalent to prevent them from flying off during removal.

(4) Disengage the 2 claws as shown in the illustration to remove the radiator grille emblem assembly.

Remove in this Direction

(d) w/o Slit (When Replacing the Front Bumper Cover):

(1) Using a center punch, make a depression at the positions shown in the illustration.

*1

Spring Nut

-

-

*a

Depression

*b

Pin of Radiator Grille Emblem Assembly

*c

Center Line

-

-

HINT:

  • Make sure to make the depressions so they are aligned with the center line of the pin of the radiator grille emblem assembly.
  • Make sure to make the depressions correctly so that a plier nipper (side cutters) can be used to pinch the spring nuts.

(2) Using a plier nipper (side cutters), rotate the 2 spring nuts to align the cutouts of each spring nut as shown in the illustration.

*a

90

*b

Depression

*c

Cutout

-

-

(3) Using a plier nipper (side cutters), deform each spring nut as shown in the illustration and then remove the 2 spring nuts.

*a

Cutout

-

-

Pinch

-

-

(4) Disengage the 2 claws and 2 guides as shown in the illustration to remove the radiator grille emblem assembly.

Remove in this Direction

21. REMOVE FRONT ENERGY ABSORBER MOUNTING REINFORCEMENT LH

(a) Remove the front energy absorber mounting reinforcement LH as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction

22. REMOVE FRONT ENERGY ABSORBER MOUNTING REINFORCEMENT RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the LH side.

23. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER ENERGY ABSORBER

(a) Remove the front bumper energy absorber as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction

24. REMOVE LOWER FRONT BUMPER ABSORBER

(a) Remove the 3 clips and lower front bumper absorber.

25. REMOVE RADIATOR SHUTTER SUB-ASSEMBLY

Click here

26. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER REINFORCEMENT SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Disengage the 11 clamps.

(b) Remove the 8 bolts.

(c) Disengage the 2 guides to remove the front bumper reinforcement sub-assembly.

27. REMOVE NO. 2 FRONT BUMPER REINFORCEMENT

(a) Remove the 4 nuts and No. 2 front bumper reinforcement.

28. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER EXTENSION LH

(a) Remove the 4 bolts and front bumper extension LH.

29. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER EXTENSION RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the LH side.

30. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER SIDE SUPPORT LH

(a) Remove the bolt.

(b) Disengage the clip as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction

(c) Disengage the claw as shown in the illustration to remove the front bumper side support LH.

Remove in this Direction

31. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER SIDE SUPPORT RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the LH side.
